      {
        "author": "Viviane Da Rosa",
        "author_uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115594760963948630086/reviews",
        "author_photo": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_JcJtPK-wAurdAofSP98PPvRIwWTYJnt4Wrv78_b3Q3ItVWExaQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo",
        "rating": 1,
        "text": "I had a terrible experience with Accurate Financial Solutions (AFS). They present themselves as financial consultants, but in reality, they are liars and scammers. Yara uses sweet talk and manipulative tactics to get you to sign up, making all kinds of promises \u2014 but they do NOT deliver on anything.\n\nThey promise to help you avoid court and fix your financial situation, but they end up doing the opposite: your name still ends up in court, your credit gets worse, and you lose money.\n\nOnce you sign with them, they disappear. There\u2019s no real support, no follow-through. It\u2019s all carefully scripted to sound trustworthy, but in truth, they are just con artists in disguise.\n\nIf you\u2019re in financial trouble, the best thing you can do is avoid this company completely and find real, honest help. AFS will only make things worse and leave you with even more\nstress and damage.\n\nDO NOT FALL FOR THIS SCAM. REPORT THEM. WARN OTHERS.",
